All is now set for the commencement of repatriation of the forty-eight thousand refugees of Borno extraction from Minawawo camp of the Cameroon republic billed to begin on twenty-sevenths of February 2021, following the signing of the revised standard procedure for the voluntary return of the refugees home.  This was brought to the fore at the end of the tripartite commission meeting held in Maroua. NTA reports that the meeting was attended by Nigerian delegation comprising Governor Babagana Umara Zulum, representatives of the Federal Ministry of Humanitarian Affairs, National Commission for Refugees, Migrants and Internally displaced persons, UNHCR and Cameroonian officials and other stakeholders. Mohammed Goni